President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Brent F. Nelsen as a member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting. Dr. Nelsen is currently the Chair of the South Carolina Educational Television Commission and a Professor of Political Science at Furman University. He has held these positions since 2011 and 2002, respectively. Dr. Nelsen has also served as the Chair of the Department of Political Science at Furman University from 2003 to 2009. He is a member of the South Carolina American Political Science Association, where he previously served as President from 2009 to 2010. Dr. Nelsen was first appointed to the Corporation for Public Broadcasting in 2013. He holds a B.A. from Wheaton College and an M.A. and Ph.D. from the University of Wisconsin-Madison.